{
  "texts": [
    "By using specific prompting (Appendix E.2) and the full description and schema of the database as input, we constrain the model to formulate more precise and concrete questions, which are easier to answer in the next step:",
    "Our work employs SQL queries instead of pandas to overcome the speed, storage, and scalability limitations of dataframes.",
    "The Query Agent QAgent generates a SQL query q ij and resulting tables R ij (q ij (D) = R ij) to answer the subquestions using the database information and schema:",
    "The objective of the QAgent is to minimize dist(q ij (D), q * ij (D)), where q * ij is the ground truth query and dist is a distance function between tables based on the cell metrics in (Papicchio et al., 2023).",
    "More concretely, we define dist as the harmonic mean of the metrics cell-precision and cell-recall, dist = 2•cell-precision•cell-recall cell-precision+cell-recall."
  ]
}